To_tsvector OR to_tsquery: Used to convert document into vector a full text search

For this challenge you need to create a simple SELECT statement. Your task is to create
a query and do a FULL TEXT SEARCH. You must search the product table on the field name for
the word Awesome and return each row with the given word. Your query MUST contain to_tsvector
and to_tsquery PostgreSQL functions.

SELECT * FROM product WHERE to_tsvector(name) @@ to_tsquery('Awesome')

https://www.codewars.com/kata/581676828906324b8b00059e/train/sql

https://www.postgresql.org/docs/current/textsearch-controls.html#TEXTSEARCH-PARSING-DOCUMENTS

